@Node "HISTOR_UPL" "Upl - History - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996-97 - Digital Design"

History
+-----+

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Upl - S.Gillibrand 1996-97 - Digital Design
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

01-Nov-95
v0.00  -+- ** STARTED PROGRAMMING ** -+-

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

...Endless Beta's :-) <Hello Tom :-)>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

03-Feb-96
v1.0  -+- ** First Public Release ** -+-

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

12-Feb-96 -> 13-May-96
v1.1

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fixes:
------

Removed the text in the Installer script that instructed you to do something
with upl.trans regarding some flags and access levels. (That's what you get
from cut&pasting ;))

Upl now realises when NO files have been uploaded and doesn't give loads of
time to the user for free :-).

Upl will now process files with paths different from UPLOAD area.
(e.g. when UFT/etc. has changed the filepath via T:Xfers.temp to a bad dir)

Local file path/filename handling totally re-written. Now you can upload from
ANYWHERE on your HDD and not have to worry about UFt/etc. going ape shit :)

Local String uploading (if C:Requestfile is missing) hadn't been finished off
://. You couldn't escape the deadly loop :-). Now you can.

When switching to uploads area 'Upl' now actually MOVES into that file area
instead of just placing the uploads there. This fixes the problems with UpTest
(UFT) and maybe some other programme that expect to find uploads in the
current area.

Upl now indicates Infinite byte ratio if it equals 0 or 255, as with the file
ratio.

Upl now detects when nothing was entered with the File Requester (C:Requestfile)
on local logon and will quit out.

Carrier detection is now present in Description entering and if the user drops
DTR during this then Upl will give the file a descripion of:
	"[Upl]: User Dropped Carrier During Desc!".

Fixed numerous internal errors/fixes/etc. - Now operates a lot faster & cleaner.

Doh!! - Removed the double copying in local upload parsing - Now 200% faster :).

Damn! Due to arexx only parsing the first 1000 characters with ReadLn() I now
have to use ReadCh() so the local upload parsing is slower. This needed to be
done as if you uploaded a lot of local files half of them got ignored :((.

Additions:
----------

Informs users which (if any) of their files failed to exist in the upload path
, so they don't wonder what's going on when they see "0" files uploaded.

Dupe checking added, external C programmes are used to SUPER FAST check for
duplicate filenames (Of course coded by moi =]).

If Upl switches to "Uploads Area" then just before it terminates Upl now moves
back to the area the user was in before he/she uploaded.

Implemented IceArc (See archive inside this archive!) for virus checking via
VirusZ, VirusChecker & VirusWorkshop.

Upl now works with Non-Batch protocols.

Implemented [Time Bonus Via Bytes] aswell as [Time Taken].

Upl now tells off naughty users who upload files with spaces in their filename
and strips the spaces off for them :).

Dupe checking is now carried out via 2 external C programmes (By me of course :))
so Upl is now beginning to look like the next generation UFT.

User can now enter _ANY_ line of description as "\sysop" to move the upload
into the SysOp's personal area (Like PC's Remote Access S/W :)).

Now checks to see if the user also uploaded an "Aminet (c) style" .README file
and if so checks it for a SHORT: description which the user can use as part
of his / her description entering :) - Checks for SEPERATE uploaded file AND
in the archive for .README file! - 50%++ chance of finding an auto-desc :-).

It is now possible to specify which directory the requestor will jump to first
upon a local upload.

Now supports multiline BBS systems.

Now an option to check if a filename is online before you upload.

Option to pack description into archive/file as File_ID.DIZ if one isn't
present with optional 1 line bbsad/etc. tagged on.

Displays the amount of bytes & overall percent saved by deleteing specific
file(s) from archive.

Adds date & time and version of Upl to Filenote of NEWly packed DIZ if option
is enabled.

Skips .README files that have been uploaded seperatley but allready used by
Upl for another file's description.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

14-May-96 -> 21-Mar-97 (!)
v1.2

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fixes:
------

Removed possible crash point when Upl checks for Aminet style ".readme" files
in the uploaded file(s).

Removed crash whereby if files.bbs didn't exist in the badfiles area Upl
would bomb!! :~(.

Additions:
----------

Added check for file named "ram:Upl_Jump" which will cause Upl to jump to
processing the files held in t:Xfers[_x].temp (Useful to put in your hydra
scripts / etc. whereby files have already been sent).

Changed priority of certain pieces of code to improve functionality and general
speed.

Added "batch descripter" for quick local uploads.

Updated the executables and included the source code (.c) in the distro.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

21-Mar-97 -> 29-Mar-97
v1.21

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fixes:
------

Fixed "icearc.bbs" bug, upl now looks for the proper file "icearc.brain" as
used by the "IceArc" distribution found inside Upl. MUCH thanks go to
Wolfgang Ernicke for pointing this out (Cheers).

Additions:
----------

Sorry guys NONE, wait for the next version, or e-mail me some new ideas :)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

	---Eof.

@EndNode

