@Node "VARIABLES_UPL" "Upl - Varibles Rundown - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996-97 - Digital Design"

Listed here are the variables at the top of the Upl.Trans file and how to use them:

---[Unarcd]--

Template: unarcd=<path>
Example : unarcd="T:"
Usage   : FULL Path of temporary directory for Upl.

---[Descln]---

Template: descln=<integer>
Example : descln=10
Usage   : Maximum number of lines a user can enter for 1 file description.

---[MaxDiz]---

Template: maxdiz=<integer>
Example : maxdiz=15
Usage   : Maximum number of lines taken from FILE_ID.DIZ as description.

---[UplDev]---

Template: upldev=<device>
Example : upldev="BBS:"
Usage   : Actual DEVICE of upload drive (BBS:Uploads/Line0/ would be "BBS:").

---[Switch]---

Template: switch=<integer>
Example : switch=1
Usage   : Area number to switch to if user doesn't have access to current.

--[Logging]---

Template: logging=<boolean>
Example : logging=1
Usage   : Log to TransAmiga.Log? - Boolean [True/False] 0=No, 1=Yes.

--[Bonus Type]--

Template: bonustype=<integer>
Example : bonustype=1
Usage   : Which Type of bonus to enforce? - -1 = NO BONUS!, 0 = Time BONUS
                                             1 = Byte BONUS

if "0":

	--[UlBonus]---
	
	Template: ulbonus=<integer>
	Example : ulbonus=2
	Usage   : Amount to multiply time taken to upload by;
	          Time taken to upload gets modified by this then this value
	          is 'refunded' to the current time left online.
	          >0 = Bonus, 0 = No Bonus (Straight Refund), -1 = No Refund!

if "1":

	--[ByBonus]---
	
	Template: bybonus=<integer>
	Example : bybonus=1500
	Usage   : Give 1 second time bonus for every "bybonus" uploaded byte(s).
	          In the example - 100k uploaded would result in:
	          102400/1500=68.266666667 (68 seconds) (1 Minute) bonus.
	          

else "No Bonus":

	!! Poor user :) !!

--[Dupe Check]--

Template: dupecheck=<boolean>
Example : dupecheck=1
Usage   : Check every file for duplicate? Boolean [True/False] 0=No, 1=Yes.

if "1":

	--[SUpl Path]--
	
	Template: suplpath=<Path>
	Example : suplpath="BBS:Bin/SUpl"
	Usage   : The full path to the SUpl executable as distributed with Upl.

	--[List Path]--
	
	Template: listpath=<Path>
	Example : listpath="BBS:Misc/Dupelist"
	Usage   : The full path to the "Dupelist" as created by "DUpl" earlier.

	--[Dupe Action]--
	
	Template: dupeact=<Option>
	Example : dupeact="M"
	Usage   : Action to take upon Duplicate Found - See "--[Actions]--" below!

--[Bad Area]--

Template: badarea=<Path>
Example : badarea="File:Badfiles/"
Usage   : Full path to where you wish to toss "bad files" to if "action" is
          requested to move a file (See Below).

--[Virus Action]--

Template: vrusact=<Option>
Example : vrusact="D"
Usage   : Action to take upon Virus Found - See "--[Actions]--" below!

--[Badlist Action]--

Template: blstact=<Option>
Example : blstact="M"
Usage   : Action to take upon filename found in the BadList
          See "--[Actions]--" below!

--[Virus Check]--

Template: viruscheck=<Boolean>
Example : viruscheck=1
Usage   : Check archive/file for virii? Boolean [True/False] 0=No, 1=Yes.

if "1":

	--[VirusZ Path]--
	
	Template: viruszpath=<Path>
	Example : viruszpath="Work:Util/VirusZII/VirusZ"
	Usage   : The full path to the VirusZ path executable, which will be used
	          if it isn't allready running.

	--[Quit VirusZ]--
	
	Template: quitvz=<Boolean>
	Example : quitvz=1
	Usage   : Quit VirusZ afterwards (if it was run by Upl)?
	          Boolean [True/False] 0=No, 1=Yes.

	--[UnArc Path]--
	
	Template: unarcpath=<Path>
	Example : unarcpath="Mail:UplTest"
	Usage   : Full path to unarchive files to via IceArc (RAM not reccomended!).

	--[Maximum Size]--
	
	Template: maxsize=<Integer Bytes>
	Example : maxsize=204800         (2Meg)
	Usage   : Maximum ARCHIVED size to unarchive, if size exceeds this then
	          the file alone will be checked for virii.

--[Add File]--

Template: addfile=<Path/Wildcard>
Example : addfile="BBS:Misc/DigitalDesign.Displayme"
Usage   : File(s) to add to all archived uploads via IceArc (Leave blank if none
          are desired).

--[Delete File]--

Template: delfile=<Path/Wildcard>
Example : delfile="(#?.displayme|#?.foo)"
Usage   : File(s) to delete from all archived uploads via IceArc (Leave blank if
          none are desired). [Note: Files are deleted from archive FIRST before
          any specified above are added].

--[Bad List]--

Template: badlist=<Path>
Example : badlist="BBS:Configs/Upl.Badfiles"
Usage   : Full path to the badfiles list - This file should contain filenames
          each on their own line, if a file is uploaded which matches any of
          these filenames then they/it will be acted upon in accordance to how
          "blstact" (See Above) is set.

--[SysOp Area]--

Template: sysoparea=<Path>
Example : sysoparea="File:Filesforsysop/"
Usage   : The full path to a directory that files for the sysop (As specifed by
          the user at upload time by entering a "\sysop" on any description
          line) will be moved to.

--[Check Readme]--

Template: checkrm=<Boolean>
Example : checkrm=1
Usage   : Check for Aminet® Style .readme files in the uploads, if the file was
          unarchived (i.e. virus checking is active) then each *.readme inside
          that archive is checked for a valid Aminet® .readme format file and
          will be used, otherwise Upl will check for upload of a .README file
          seperatley. 1=Yes, 0=No.

--[Requestor Path]--

Template: reqpath=<Path>
Example : reqpath="Usr:PsychOEd/"
Usage   : The path that the requestor will automatically jump to as soon as it
          appears upon Local Upload.

--[New File_ID.DIZ]--

Template: newdiz=<Boolean>
Example : newdiz=1
Usage   : If File_ID.DIZ wasn't found in file attempt to pack user description
          into archive as File_ID.DIZ?. 1=Yes, 0=No.

	--[File_ID.DIZ One Liner BBS Ad/Etc.]--

	Template: dizbbsad=<45 Character MAX String>
	Example : dizbbsad="-[. Digital Dreams Amiga * 44-1772-454995 .]-"
	Usage   : If above option is set to ON, then Upl will add this string to the
	          end of it as a 1 line BBS-Ad/etc.

--[Batch Descriptor Text]--

Template: awaiting=<string (max 40 char)>
Example : awaiting="[Upl] Awaiting description!"
Usage   : If locally uploading and "batch descriptors" is enabled then this will
          be used for the file description if NO file_id.diz OR aminet description
          is found.

**--[Actions]--** (These can be used by 3 aforementioned functions)

Template: ="D/M/C/K"
Example : n/a
Usage   : D = delete file and give NO credit and ask for NO description,
          M = move file and give NO credit and ask for NO description.
          C = move file and give credit and ask for description.
          K = keep file and give credit and ask for description.

@EndNode

@Node "TUPLDATA_UPL" "Upl - Upl Data File Format - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996-97 - Digital Design"

Whenever Upl is invoked and processes uploads it creates a file in T: under the
following filename:

T:Upl_<BBS Line Number>.Dat

This file may be put to good use in the "AfterUl.Trans" file.
The format follows:

(All lines preceded with a ";" aren't in the produced file!)

; Upl signature purely for authenticity.
@-UplData
<Files Uploaded>
; Then for each file uploaded the following lines:
<Filename>
<Filepath>
<Filesize>
; #desc to define beginning of file description
#desc
<Description....>
<Description....>
<etc.>
; #endesc to define end of file description
#endesc
<Big Description (1=Yes 0=No)>
<File Credit Given>
<Bytes Credit Given>
; After the files data the following is listed:
<Total Bytes Uploaded>
<Total File Credit Given>
<Total Byte Credit Given>
<Files Available Before Next Upload>
<Bytes Available Before Next Upload>
<Time Taken By Upload(s) And Description Entering>
<Time Awarded For Upload(s)>
<Time Left On-Line Today>


An example of the above file follows from a local upload on my BBS:

T:Upl_0.Dat

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@-UplData
5
A8filecfgspam.rexx
BBS:BBSUploads/A8filecfgspam.rexx
756
#desc
Aminet8 CDRom File.Cfg Spammer For TA   
#endesc
0
255
0
A8Spam.rexx
BBS:BBSUploads/A8Spam.rexx
733
#desc
Aminet8 CDRom Files.BBS/DIr Spammer For 
TA v1.2+                                
#endesc
0
255
0
agony.gif
BBS:BBSUploads/agony.gif
36875
#desc
Hand draw picture from the Party 95'    
                                        
                      Randall/Subs      
#endesc
0
255
0
Installer.doc
BBS:BBSUploads/Installer.doc
63788
#desc
Commodore Installer Documentation       
#endesc
0
255
0
TAED.Functions
BBS:BBSUploads/TAED.Functions
770
#desc
ASCII List                              
                                        
List of TAEd (Issued with TA) functions 
for use by some programme somewhere :)  
#endesc
0
255
0
102922
1275
0
Infinite
Infinite
3
6
74

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@EndNode

@Node "EXTERNALC_UPL" "Upl - External C Progammes - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996-97 - Digital Design"

There exist 3 external programmes that work in conjunction with Upl for speed
and features. These area:

1) SUpl

	This is fully automatic and only needs to be placed in the path specified
	in Upl.Trans for Upl to work correctly - Basically it analyzes the Dupe
	File created with DUpl (See Below) and prints information to the TransAmiga
	screen and the online user.

2) DUpl

	This file should be run every night in the midnight script or similair!
	DUpl requires some command line parameters, these being:

	DUpl <File.Cfg Path> <Dupe File Destination Path>

	An example being:- "DUpl bbs:configs/file.cfg bbs:misc/dupelist"

	DUpl creates a list of ALL filenames from the BBS filebase as listed
	in "file.cfg" and places them on the destination path specified.
	Running this file every night ensures that Upl has a 90% chance of
	catching duplicates that users/YOU (:)) upload. Please make sure
	the destination path you specify here matches up with the one in the
	Upl.Trans file! - If you want to be DEADLY sure run this in your
	logoff.trans, but that's being a bit TOO crazy? isn't it??! :)
	Incase I didn't mention, DUpl is blisteringly fast, maybe Sami should
	take some coding tips from me? :))

3) IceArc

	Now this is MINT (Or so my co-sysop Jay says :)), this is a Multi-Format
	(de)archiver and to put it simply it RULES, if you want more info look
	inside the IceArc archive included in this Upl archive.
	The way Upl uses IceArc is fairly obvious really, it uses it to unarchive
	files as they come in so as to check inside them for virii.
	The latest version of IceArc is always on the Aminet/My BBS and FREQ
	as "ICEARC" from me also.

	N.B. IceArc is automatically unarchived with the Commodore Installer
	script.

@EndNode
